node.text:
Eccentric-focused training is a great way to work on a bit of everything

Working on your eccentrics builds size, strength, stability and flexibility all in one - a great all-rounder, and perfect for those starting strength training

Here’s a home workout targeting the upper body for you to try - all you need are 2 chairs and a towel

1️⃣ Push Up 4x8 (add weight onto your mid-back to progress - bag full of textbooks work great)
2️⃣ Tricep Dip 3x10 (progress by adding weight onto your lap - use the same bag)
3️⃣ Bench Pull 4x8 (wear that bag across your chest to progress)
4️⃣ Towel Row 3x10 (progress by doing single arm eccentrics as shown)

The key here is time under tension. We’re looking for extended time in the eccentric phase, through a controlled, constant, purposeful movement. Start with 3s eccentrics and work your way up to 8s eccentrics (and then progress the exercise once you’ve mastered that)
